'A narrow band of wavelength', a collection of monochromes inspired artwork, was officially opened during a private viewing cocktail at the Sankara Nairobi Hotel on Tuesday evening.The exhibition brought together five artists from diverse areas to showcase the black and white theme in different ways.Also being showcased were highly sculpted wooden materials from Baldy Osborne, Thom Ogonga, Charles Kamya, Farrah Akbarali and Morris Foit.The collection shall be on show for four months at the hotel.